abstract: The Democratic contenders hoping to challenge President Donald Trump in November 2020 all argue the Republican leader's unorthodox foreign policy approach has endangered American interests.

abstract: A Democratic push to force Republicans to accept witnesses at President Donald Trump's impeachment trial in the U.S. Senate appeared to be flagging on Wednesday, raising the possibility he could be acquitted as early as Friday.
snippet: A Democratic push to force Republicans to accept witnesses at President Donald Trump's impeachment trial in the U.S. Senate appeared to be flagging on Wednesday, raising the possibility he could be acquitted as early as Friday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A Democratic push to force Republicans to accept witnesses at President Donald Trump's impeachment trial in the U.S. Senate appeared to be flagging on Wednesday, raising the possibility he could be acquitted as early as Friday.
headline_main: Republicans Hopeful Senate Will Acquit Trump in Impeachment Trial as Early as Friday
headline_print_headline: Republicans Hopeful Senate Will Acquit Trump in Impeachment Trial as Early as Friday

abstract: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said on Tuesday that a U.S. peace plan envisages the proposed Palestinian capital be located in Abu Dis, a neighbourhood on the outskirts of Jerusalem.
snippet: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said on Tuesday that a U.S. peace plan envisages the proposed Palestinian capital be located in Abu Dis, a neighbourhood on the outskirts of Jerusalem.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said on Tuesday that a U.S. peace plan envisages the proposed Palestinian capital be located in Abu Dis, a neighbourhood on the outskirts of Jerusalem.
headline_main: Netanyahu Says Proposed Palestinian Capital Will Be in Abu Dis
headline_print_headline: Netanyahu Says Proposed Palestinian Capital Will Be in Abu Dis

abstract: A deep-in-debt Michael Avenatti threatened to deploy his big social media and television presence like a “modern weapon” to try to extort up to $25 million from Nike, a prosecutor claimed Wednesday while a lawyer for the California attorney told jurors at a trial's opening not to criminalize his client's “aggressive, tenacious, demanding behavior.”
snippet: A deep-in-debt Michael Avenatti threatened to deploy his big social media and television presence like a “modern weapon” to try to extort up to $25 million from Nike, a prosecutor claimed Wednesday while a lawyer for the California attorney told j...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — A deep-in-debt Michael Avenatti threatened to deploy his big social media and television presence like a “modern weapon” to try to extort up to $25 million from Nike, a prosecutor claimed Wednesday while a lawyer for the California attorney told jurors at a trial's opening not to criminalize his client's “aggressive, tenacious, demanding behavior.”
headline_main: Prosecutor: Michael Avenatti Saw Dollar Signs in Nike Fraud
headline_print_headline: Prosecutor: Michael Avenatti Saw Dollar Signs in Nike Fraud

abstract: Alan Dershowitz told the Senate a “quid pro quo” to help the president’s re-election is by definition in the national interest.
snippet: Alan Dershowitz told the Senate a “quid pro quo” to help the president’s re-election is by definition in the national interest.
lead_paragraph: Alan Dershowitz, one of President Trump’s impeachment lawyers, pushed an extraordinarily expansive view of executive power during his trial on Wednesday, arguing that any action taken by the president to help his own re-election is, by definition, in the public interest.

headline_main: Anything a president does to stay in power is in the national interest, Dershowitz argues.

abstract: As Bernie Sanders shows strength in the early-voting states, his opponents face a challenge: Attacking him can help fuel his campaign.
snippet: As Bernie Sanders shows strength in the early-voting states, his opponents face a challenge: Attacking him can help fuel his campaign.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — A Democratic super PAC wanted to undermine Senator Bernie Sanders’s presidential candidacy just days before the Iowa caucuses. It may have handed him a gift instead.

abstract: Just as the outlook for the global economy had been brightening in recent months, a new threat has suddenly emerged in the form of the viral outbreak in China.
snippet: Just as the outlook for the global economy had been brightening in recent months, a new threat has suddenly emerged in the form of the viral outbreak in China.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Just as the outlook for the global economy had been brightening in recent months, a new threat has suddenly emerged in the form of the viral outbreak in China.
headline_main: Fed Chair Sees China Virus as Possible Risk to World Economy
headline_print_headline: Fed Chair Sees China Virus as Possible Risk to World Economy

abstract: Global equity markets closed little changed on Wednesday as strong results from Apple and others provided a lift, but concerns about the coronavirus outbreak in China kept enthusiasm in check and a safe-haven bid in gold and the dollar alive.
snippet: Global equity markets closed little changed on Wednesday as strong results from Apple and others provided a lift, but concerns about the coronavirus outbreak in China kept enthusiasm in check and a safe-haven bid in gold and the dollar alive.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Global equity markets closed little changed on Wednesday as strong results from Apple and others provided a lift, but concerns about the coronavirus outbreak in China kept enthusiasm in check and a safe-haven bid in gold and the dollar alive.
headline_main: Global Stock Rally Loses Steam, Virus Keeps Safe-Havens Alive
headline_print_headline: Global Stock Rally Loses Steam, Virus Keeps Safe-Havens Alive

abstract: General Dynamics on Wednesday reported a 28% jump in its order backlog due to an order for Navy submarines, and quarterly profits that topped Wall Street estimates helped by higher sales in its aerospace unit that makes Gulfstream business jets.
snippet: General Dynamics on Wednesday reported a 28% jump in its order backlog due to an order for Navy submarines, and quarterly profits that topped Wall Street estimates helped by higher sales in its aerospace unit that makes Gulfstream business jets.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - General Dynamics on Wednesday reported a 28% jump in its order backlog due to an order for Navy submarines, and quarterly profits that topped Wall Street estimates helped by higher sales in its aerospace unit that makes Gulfstream business jets.
headline_main: General Dynamics Tops Profit Estimates; Submarine Order Beefs Up Backlog
headline_print_headline: General Dynamics Tops Profit Estimates; Submarine Order Beefs Up Backlog
